ğŸ”„ 3-Phase Workflow
Phase 1: Extract & Dict
What it does:
Extracts new/updated text from new game version
Compares with old mod version
Creates clean_for_translation.txt (only lines that need translation)
Runs Auto-Extract Dict (finds game codes to preserve, e.g., [planet_type], $LEADER$)

Output:
clean_for_translation.txt â†’ File to translate
Dict.txt â†’ Auto-updated, sorted by length

Waits for user:
âœ… Review Dict.txt (remove errors, add needed words)
âœ… Click Confirm when ready

Time: 2-5 minutes (depends on file size)
Phase 2: Prepare for Translation
What it does:
Clean & Sort Dict (remove duplicates, sort by length)
Replace Dict words with Unicode symbol (ğ“³)
Remove duplicate lines (reduces lines to translate)
Creates _unique.txt and _unique_Backup.txt

Output:
converted_text_XXXXXX_unique.txt â†’ Send to AI for translation
converted_text_XXXXXX_unique_Backup.txt â†’ For validation

Waits for user:
ğŸ¤– Send _unique.txt to AI for translation (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, etc.)
ğŸ“¥ Import translated file via Tab 4 (or in Confirmation Dialog)
âœ… Click Confirm when translation complete and imported

Time: 1-3 minutes (excluding translation time)
Example line reduction:
Original: 5,000 lines
After deduplication: 3,200 lines (36% savings)


Phase 3: Merge & Complete
What it does:
Restore translations to duplicate lines
Replace Unicode symbol (ğ“³) back to original game codes
Merge translations back into game file structure
Creates Mod folder Updated_Thai_Translation

Output:
ğŸ“ output/Updated_Thai_Translation/ â†’ Ready-to-use mod
âœ… Can be used in game immediately

Time: 3-8 minutes (depends on number of files)
ğŸ›¡ï¸ Symbol Validation System
Why is it needed?
Stellaris uses special symbols for display:

ğ“³ = Variables that must be preserved
\n = Line breaks

If AI translation loses, adds, or changes the count â†’ Game will display incorrectly
How does it work?

Auto-Check when importing translated file
Counts ğ“³ and \n in each line
Compares with original file
If mismatch:

Creates Error_line.txt (lines with errors)
Creates Original_Compare_Line.txt (original lines for reference)
Creates Error_line_mapping.txt (line positions)
Shows Error Dialog with instructions


User fixes Error_line.txt to match original
Click Confirm â†’ System auto-replaces
Re-validates until 100% correct
Example:

âœ… Correct:
Original: "Planet ğ“³ has ğ“³ resources\nPopulation: ğ“³"
Translate: "à¸”à¸²à¸§à¹€à¸„à¸£à¸²à¸°à¸«à¹Œ ğ“³ à¸¡à¸µà¸—à¸£à¸±à¸à¸¢à¸²à¸à¸£ ğ“³\nà¸›à¸£à¸°à¸Šà¸²à¸à¸£: ğ“³"
â†’ ğ“³ = 3, \n = 1 (match!)

âŒ Wrong:
